# IAM USER CREATION WITH GUI & CLI ACCESS (AWS)

## PART A: CREATE IAM USER (GUI ACCESS)

### STEP 1: LOGIN AS ROOT USER
1. Go to AWS Management Console  
2. Login as Root User  

---

### STEP 2: OPEN IAM
1. Search for IAM  
2. Click IAM (Security, Identity, & Compliance)  

---

### STEP 3: CREATE USER
1. Go to Users  
2. Click Create user  

---

### STEP 4: USER DETAILS
1. Enter User name: S3_Specialist  
2. Enable: Provide user access to AWS Management Console  
3. Set custom password  

---

### STEP 5: SET PERMISSIONS
1. Select Attach policies directly  
2. Search and select: AmazonS3FullAccess  

---

### STEP 6: REVIEW & CREATE
1. Click Next → Create user  
2. Download the .csv file (important credentials)  

---

### STEP 7: SIGN OUT & LOGIN AS IAM USER
1. Copy Account ID (12-digit)  
2. Sign out  
3. Use Sign-in URL from .csv OR IAM login page  
4. Enter:
   - Account ID  
   - Username  
   - Password  

---

### TESTING PERMISSIONS

#### TEST 1 (FAILURE)
1. Go to EC2  
2. Try viewing instances  
Result: Access Denied / API Error  

#### TEST 2 (SUCCESS)
1. Go to S3  
2. Create a bucket  
Result: Success  

---

## PART B: CLI ACCESS (PROGRAMMATIC ACCESS)

### STEP 1: GENERATE ACCESS KEYS
1. Go to IAM → Users  
2. Click your user  
3. Open Security credentials tab  
4. Scroll to Access keys  
5. Click Create access key  
6. Select: Command Line Interface (CLI)  
7. Download .csv (contains keys)  

---

### STEP 2: INSTALL AWS CLI (WINDOWS)
Run in Command Prompt:

msiexec.exe /i https://awscli.amazonaws.com/AWSCLIV2.msi
msiexec.exe /i https://awscli.amazonaws.com/AWSCLIV2.msi/qn
aws --version

---

### STEP 3: CONFIGURE AWS CLI
1. Open CMD / Terminal  
2. Run:
aws configure

3. Enter:
- Access Key ID  
- Secret Access Key  
- Default region: ap-south-1  
- Default output: json  

---

### STEP 4: TEST CLI PERMISSIONS

#### TEST 1 (EC2 - FAILURE)
aws ec2 describe-instances
Result: AccessDenied error  

---

#### TEST 2 (S3 - SUCCESS)
aws s3 ls
aws s3 mb s3://your-unique-bucket-name

Result: Success  

---

## CONCLUSION
- IAM user has restricted access (only S3)  
- GUI and CLI both enforce same permissions  
- EC2 access denied, S3 operations allowed  
